9:39 AM Defendant Joshua William Edward Alewine in court.  Attorney Chris A Gramstrup in court for Joshua William Edward Alewine.  Prosecuting attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Case is on for Sentencing Hearing. Court notes Count 3 is now under a deferred agreement, and will not consider that count in sentencing today. State assures VR compliance.  Parties acknowledge receipt of PSI, propose no corrections or modifications.  State argues for probation with a 1 year jail imposed/stayed on Count 1, not opposed to expungement.  Defense attorney argues for DOC recommendations with expungement.  Defendant makes a statement.  
Court orders:
Count 1: Vehicle operator flee/elude officer- 1 year probation, 9 months jail imposed and stayed; consecutive to Count 6
Conditions:  Gainful employment.  No use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Court costs of $250 DNA only.  Bond to be applied and def to pay remaining $126 today.  Def may have this count expunged if he successfully completes probation when he completes probation.  
Count 6: OWI (2nd)- 
Fine inclusive of costs totaling $876 
DL revoked for 12 months
IID must be installed on any vehicle def owns, possesses, or intends to drive for 12 months
OWI assessment and driver safety plan
5 days, jail, 2 days jail credit; eligible for electronic monitoring and good time

Sentencing hearing on October 3, 2022 at 09:30 am.

11:32 AM Cases 22CF109, 2022TR000304, 2022TR000308, 2022TR000309.  Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Agreement is recited by Attorney Gramstrup: def pleading to Cts 1: flee/elude, 3: 2nd Deg Reckless Endangering Safety, and 6: OWI (2nd) in 22CF109; DRI remaining cases and counts; request PSI, State agrees not to argue for any executed confinement time.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Off the record 11:36 AM.  Back on the record 11:41 AM, same appearances.  State updates: will do DJOC on plea to Ct 3; 5 yr agreement, will draft agreement prior to sentencing.  Court reviews Def's constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for pleas.  Def enters Guilty pleas.  Court finds def is making pleas knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the pleas.  Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 1, 3, and 6 and orders a JOC; Counts 2, 4, 5 DRI; Count 7 is merged in with Count 6; TR matters DRI.  Court orders PSI, long form, agent does not need to be present, but should be available by phone- if needed- for sentencing hearing.  Court will adopt the DJOC on Count 3 once the paperwork is signed and filed.  Bond to continue.
